2 unit(s) Apple
1 sachet(s) Ground Cinnamon
220 grams Yoghurt
120 grams Granola
5 tsp Sugar
to taste Water

Peel, quarter and core the apples.
Finely chop.

Add apples, cinnamon, 2 tbsp of water and 5 tsp sugar to a medium pot over medium heat.
Cook until the apple begins to soften, 7-8 mins.
Set aside to cool, 5 mins.

Divide yoghurt between serving bowls.
Mix the granola through the apples.
To finish, spoon the yoghurt over the top.